.TH "__netdev_notify_peers" 9 "__netdev_notify_peers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__netdev_notify_peers \- notify network peers about existence of @dev, to be called when rtnl lock is already held.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __netdev_notify_peers
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
network device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generate traffic such that interested network peers are aware of
\fIdev\fP, such as by generating a gratuitous ARP. This may be used when
a device wants to inform the rest of the network about some sort of
reconfiguration such as a failover event or virtual machine
migration.
